The Dental Academy is designed to introduce students to a variety of dental health professions and experience to promote the dental professions.

The Dental Academy is open to all students who are in Grades 9 thru 12.
<h3>Hands-on Experiences include</h3>
<ul>
	<li>Job Shadowing with Dentists, Dental Hygienists and Dental Assistants during a variety of procedures</li>
	<li>Dental impressions (ie molds of mouth)</li>
	<li>Suturing</li>
	<li>Practice on a Dental Simulator (computerized, robotic patient) with UNE College of Dental Medicine</li>
	<li>CPR Certification</li>
	<li>Dental X-Rays</li>
	<li>Career Planning</li>
	<li>HIPAA</li>
	<li>Bloodborne Pathogens and Infection Control</li>
</ul>
Each day begins at 9:00 am at PCHC Dental Center,¬† 1048 Union Street, Bangor and concludes at 3:30 pm.
<h3>How to participate</h3>
<strong></strong>Only 10 candidates will be accepted for this second annual dental career experience. Students will be
accepted on a first-come basis with completed application form and positive school recommendations.
<ul>
	<li>Students in Grades 9 thru Grade 12 are eligible to participate.</li>
	<li>[wpfilebase tag=fileurl id=35 linktext=Applications /]¬†can be download or contact¬†Amanda¬†Klausing¬†at¬†<a href="mailto:aklausing@pchc.com" target="_blank">aklausing@pchc.com</a>¬†to have one emailed to you. You may also call 992-9200 to have one mailed.</li>
