Set at Penobscot Community Health Care, Maine's largest and most comprehensive community health center system, residents will work with a broad patient base - head to toe, pediatrics to geriatrics.

The purpose of the PCHC NP Residency Program is to provide residents clinical experience in an integrated primary care environment.¬† Residents will receive an intense clinical training that is necessary to serve as primary care providers in the complex setting of the country‚Äôs Federally Qualified Health Centers (FQHCs).¬† Residents will also work to improve their clinical skills, confidence, and productivity using state-of-the-art technology in a patient-centered practice setting.

The one-year program will provide residents a depth of complexity in patient care and clinical experience.¬† As the greater Bangor region's safety net provider, PCHC sees a population of patients that are uninsured, underinsured, and homeless patients.¬† Residents will learn how social factors such as mental illness, substance, poverty, and rurality impacts patient health outcomes.

As a new NP, the PCHC NP Residency Program will enhance your preparation to meet the challenge of primary care.";s:10:"post_title";s:41:"PCHC Nurse Practitioner Residency Program";s:12:"post_excerpt";s:0:"";s:11:"post_status";s:7:"publish";s:14:"comment_status";s:6:"closed";s:11:"ping_status";s:4:"open";s:13:"post_password";s:0:"";s:9:"post_name";s:41:"pchc-nurse-practitioner-residency-program";s:7:"to_ping";s:0:"";s:6:"pinged";s:0:"";s:13:"post_modified";s:19:"2013-09-16 12:09:51";s:17:"post_modified_gmt";s:19:"2013-09-16 16:09:51";s:21:"post_content_filtered";s:0:"";s:11:"post_parent";s:2:"58";s:4:"guid";s:32:"http://www.pchc.com/?page_id=438";s:10:"menu_order";s:1:"0";s:9:"post_type";s:4:"page";s:14:"post_mime_type";s:0:"";s:13:"comment_count";s:1:"0";}i:3;O:8:"stdClass":23:{s:2:"ID";s:3:"433";s:11:"post_author";s:1:"5";s:9:"post_date";s:19:"2013-09-16 12:03:34";s:13:"post_date_gmt";s:19:"2013-09-16 16:03:34";s:12:"post_content";s:4843:"<h4>Residency is just the first step! Our program prepares pharmacists for clinical patient care positions in integrated healthcare models, academic faculty positions, or PGY2 training.</h4>
<strong>Penobscot Community Health Care (PCHC) is a non-profit Federally Qualified Health Center (FQHC) established in 1998, and is by far the largest and most comprehensive of Maine‚Äôs nineteen FQHCs.</strong>

Last year, PCHC provided 330,000 visits to nearly 60,000 patients. With over 600 employees, 170 providers and 15 different clinics, PCHC provides patient centered, comprehensive, integrated care in a variety of clinical services, including on site pharmacy services.

PCHC is the only ambulatory care center in Maine to be accredited by the Joint Commission and is certified as a Primary Care Medical Home. Our

Most recently, PCHC has joined Eastern Maine Health System‚Äôs Accountable Care Organizations, in our effort to pioneer integrated and seamless healthcare transitions. As part of an ACO, PCHC provides the unique setting for pharmacist integration into primary care.
<h4>Come visit us at Midyear!</h4>
<strong>We‚Äôll be situated at Booth #5525 during the residency showcase on Tuesday, December 10th during the AM Session.</strong>
<h2>About the Pharmacy Practice Residency</h2>
As a resident at PCHC, you‚Äôre immersed in the diverse areas of ambulatory care, including outpatient clinic visits, policy and program development, consulting providers, and administrating immunizations.

Providers at PCHC are extremely receptive to pharmacists in the clinics, and rely on residents for drug information and cost-effective therapy management. As a resident, you not only become fully involved within the pharmacies, but expand to teach other departments specific drug therapies, work with care managers and social workers to improve patient adherence, and create topic discussions for provider meetings.

PCHC is devoted to learning, and has partnered with both Husson College of Pharmacy and University of New England. As a PCHC resident, you will earn a teaching certificate, and educate future pharmacists.
<h3>Pharmacy Services</h3>
PCHC‚Äôs pharmacies operate under HRSA‚Äôs 340B Drug Pricing Program, stretching scare federal resources to reach more eligible patients and provide more comprehensive services.

PCHC clinics and pharmacies also participate in Affordable Care Programs, and fill over 100,000 prescriptions a year. We believe in providing patient centered, high-quality care for all patients, regardless of their ability to pay.
<h3><a href="http://www.pchc.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/09/pharmacy_lg.jpg"><img class="alignright size-medium wp-image-435" alt="Brewer Medical Center Pharmacy" src="http://www.pchc.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/09/pharmacy_lg-300x200.jpg" width="300" height="200" /></a>Available Rotations</h3>
<ul>
	<li>Management and Operations</li>
	<li>Patient Care Services (Staffing)</li>
	<li>Family Medicine</li>
	<li>Integrated Mental Health</li>
	<li>Geriatrics</li>
	<li>Pediatrics</li>
	<li>Urgent Care</li>
	<li>Drug Information</li>
	<li>Teaching (Longitudinal)</li>
	<li>Cardiology</li>
</ul>
<h3>Benefits</h3>
<ul>
	<li><strong>Salary:</strong> Residents earn a 40,000 salary for a 40 hour work week.</li>
	<li><strong>Vacation:</strong> 2 weeks paid vacation, 7 holidays and your birthday.</li>
	<li><strong>Health, Dental and Vision Insurance:</strong> Available to the resident AND their spouse/domestic partner and dependents.</li>
	<li><strong>Wellness Works!:</strong> A motivational program that pairs employees with a health coach to evaluate health and improve overall well-being. Enrollees are eligible for $250 in reimbursement for purchases towards healthcare related goals. This can include reimbursement for gym memberships, weight-loss programs, sports equipment or other related health promoting activities.</li>
	<li><strong>Professional Meetings:</strong> PCHC covers travel, accommodations and some meals for residents to both the ASHP Midyear and Eastern States Conference.</li>
	<li><strong>Pharmacy Products:</strong> OTC products are available to employees at an extremely discounted rate for purchase in the company pharmacies.</li>
	<li><strong><a href="http://www.pchc.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/09/819789786.jpg"><img class="alignright size-medium wp-image-436" alt="Physical Therapy Equipment" src="http://www.pchc.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/09/819789786-300x147.jpg" width="300" height="147" /></a>Exercise Equipment:</strong> Residents have access to physical therapy equipment for personal use</li>
	<li><strong>Optional benefits:</strong>
Long Term Disability
Short term disability
401K
Flexible Spending Accounts
Long Term Care Insurance</li>
</ul>
